data.title: The Indian Biographical Dictionary (1915)/Butler, Montagu Sherard Dawes
data.text: ​Butler, Montagu Sherard Dawes, M.A.; C.I.E. 1009; Deputy Commissioner, Lahore: b. 1873: s. of Spencer Perceval Butler; Bar-at Law. Educ.: Haileybury; Pembroke College, Cambridge Scholar, First Class Classical Tripos. Parts I. and II., with special distinction in Part II., University Bhavnagar Medalist (B.A., 1894, M.A., 1898); Fellow of Pembroke 1895-1961; (President of the Union, 1895); Entered I.C.S. 1896; Settlement Officer, Kotah State, 1904-9. Dy Commissioner, Lahore, 1909, and Dy Secretary, Government of India, Home Dept, 1911; Recreations: Fencing (Public Schools bronze medallist. ​1889) tennis. Address: Calcutta, India.
